1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,619
{\an8}Of course, you're always there.

2
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:38,079
{\an8}I know you wouldn't abandon me.

3
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:39,622
{\an8}And I know you will always protect me.

4
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:44,627
{\an8}That's why I didn't get scared,
as long as I'm with you.

5
00:00:48,089 --> 00:00:49,299
{\an8}<i>Wait a minute. She?</i>

6
00:00:49,382 --> 00:00:50,175
{\an8}<i>Of course, I want to know.</i>

7
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:56,765
{\an8}When can I meet them? Can I?

8
00:00:56,848 --> 00:00:58,641
{\an8}Perfect! Can we meet them tomorrow?

9
00:01:03,104 --> 00:01:05,482
{\an8}- Just for you.
- Perfect!

10
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:11,446
{\an8}So, you're still not sleepy?

11
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:21,831
{\an8}Just a little talk, she shouts right away.

12
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:23,333
{\an8}That's because of you!

13
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:24,417
{\an8}You're so annoying!

14
00:01:24,501 --> 00:01:27,504
{\an8}You keep getting ahead of her
in making decisions in her life,

15
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:29,839
{\an8}especially in her relationship with Mikoy.

16
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:34,886
{\an8}If she wants to tell Mikoy
the truth, fine!

17
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:36,304
{\an8}If she doesn't, then don't!

18
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:48,108
{\an8}What do you mean Chiara is distracted?

19
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:50,443
{\an8}She's not distracted.
You're just not used to it

20
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:53,029
because it's your first time
seeing your daughter in love.

21
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:54,614
That's exactly why I'm worried.

22
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:01,830
{\an8}So what?

23
00:02:01,913 --> 00:02:03,540
{\an8}Let me remind you

24
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:06,751
{\an8}that our child's life has not been easy.

25
00:02:11,089 --> 00:02:12,132
{\an8}A chaotic life!

26
00:02:12,215 --> 00:02:13,842
{\an8}Since she was young,

27
00:02:13,925 --> 00:02:16,553
{\an8}she always has to keep
her eyes open all the time!

28
00:02:21,391 --> 00:02:22,892
{\an8}So just let her be.

29
00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:25,436
{\an8}Let her go crazy over Mikoy.

30
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,604
{\an8}I don't care.

31
00:02:27,355 --> 00:02:30,316
{\an8}At least now, for the first time,

32
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:33,111
{\an8}there's someone else
who will sacrifice for her.

33
00:02:57,051 --> 00:02:57,886
Right?

34
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:00,680
See!

35
00:03:01,389 --> 00:03:03,808
That's what you're good at.
You really love sleeping!

36
00:03:17,363 --> 00:03:18,114
Mikoy?

37
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:20,909
I need your help.

38
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:24,120
Why, what's wrong? Where are you?

39
00:03:26,164 --> 00:03:28,082
No! I'm just at home.

40
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:29,626
No emergency, no danger.

41
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:32,378
Then why did you call?

42
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:36,424
I have a big problem.

43
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,218
What?

44
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:43,473
What?

45
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:45,433
I need friends!

46
00:03:53,524 --> 00:03:54,859
Hey!

47
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:58,446
You know, I really want to kiss you

48
00:03:58,529 --> 00:04:00,949
because Daddy Sir
is so impressed with you.

49
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:02,116
Dad is so happy.

50
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:05,411
Can you believe it?
He even gave an extra allowance!

51
00:04:05,495 --> 00:04:07,330
Want me to treat you?

52
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:08,790
Let's watch a movie.

53
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:10,917
I'll pay for the popcorn too.

54
00:04:12,543 --> 00:04:13,836
Thanks for the offer.

55
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:18,258
But I need to catch up on my lit readings.

56
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:24,472
Do you want me to help you?

57
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:26,391
I've got it.

58
00:04:28,184 --> 00:04:30,061
So you like romantic novels.

59
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:35,066
No wonder you were so good
at being romantic last night.

60
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:41,864
Just because I'm reading this doesn't mean
I suddenly became Jane Austen.

61
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,992
I'm not romantic at all.

62
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:45,743
Yeah, right!

63
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:47,203
I don't think so.

64
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:49,914
You're actually really sweet!

65
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:52,875
I just did what you suggested.

66
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:57,547
That I use my imagination.

67
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:01,342
That I imagine the person I really like.

68
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:08,766
So, you really imagined Jennie?

69
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:10,393
Jennie?

70
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:11,728
Not Jennie.

71
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,903
It's Luisa Mae.

72
00:05:22,405 --> 00:05:23,531
Luisa Mae?

73
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:32,957
<i>Why don't you have any friends?</i>

74
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,126
I do have friends.

75
00:05:35,209 --> 00:05:37,837
But none here in Manila.

76
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,756
They're back in my hometown.

77
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,717
Since Boss Mikoy is big time now,

78
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:46,804
you should be drinking
something expensive.

79
00:05:46,888 --> 00:05:48,097
Sure!

80
00:05:55,938 --> 00:05:57,273
What is this?!

81
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:01,861
One hundred and fifty per liter.

82
00:06:01,944 --> 00:06:04,113
Tomorrow, it's plus 30.

83
00:06:04,197 --> 00:06:05,865
You walk home.

84
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,202
This won't work on Chiara.

85
00:06:11,329 --> 00:06:14,207
Of course, I'm new here in Manila.

86
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:16,292
I don't really know many people yet.

87
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:19,587
Okay, but why did you
use that as an excuse?

88
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:21,297
I couldn't think of anything else.

89
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:26,719
We just have to find some people
who can pretend to be Mikoy's friends.

90
00:06:27,386 --> 00:06:30,306
So we'll hold auditions for new friends?

91
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:33,351
Come on.

92
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,645
That's probably not necessary.

93
00:06:36,604 --> 00:06:38,564
Because if you think about it,

94
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:41,317
it looks like I already have friends here.

95
00:06:55,164 --> 00:06:56,624
What if she recognizes you?

96
00:06:56,707 --> 00:06:58,417
What if she's already spotted you?

97
00:06:58,501 --> 00:07:00,294
She probably won't notice.

98
00:07:00,378 --> 00:07:01,629
I'll handle everything.

99
00:07:01,712 --> 00:07:04,006
I'll cover for you, okay?

100
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,466
You'll handle it, and we suffer?

101
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:06,592
You'll cover for it,

102
00:07:06,676 --> 00:07:09,387
then we're the ones who fix the mess?

103
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:10,638
Hey!

104
00:07:10,721 --> 00:07:11,889
Come on!

105
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:16,686
That's extremely risky!
It could compromise our mission.

106
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:19,480
Don't say yes!

107
00:07:22,859 --> 00:07:25,069
But if Chiara finds out
that Mikoy is lying

108
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:27,613
and that he doesn't
really have any friends,

109
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,407
then he loses her trust.

110
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:33,286
And our mission
will be even more compromised.

111
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:44,297
Okay.

112
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:47,425
It's up to you, but I'll be in disguise.

113
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:49,552
You won't recognize me.

114
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:06,694
Which one there is Luisa Mae?

115
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:08,905
‪Five, six, seven…

116
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:10,031
There.

117
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:30,259
She's pretty, right?

118
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:31,677
That's Luisa Mae.

119
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:34,555
In fairness, she's stunning!

120
00:08:37,058 --> 00:08:38,309
They're good, right?

121
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:42,897
And she's so kind too.

122
00:08:56,953 --> 00:08:59,580
Huh? Of course, definitely!

123
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:00,831
Sweetheart, come on.

124
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:05,294
They'll definitely like you.

125
00:09:06,629 --> 00:09:07,588
Where are your friends?

126
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:10,258
- Mikoy!
- There!

127
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:12,093
Sianong!

128
00:09:23,854 --> 00:09:25,481
Good to see you, bro!

129
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,525
Huh?

130
00:09:34,282 --> 00:09:38,494
Finally! Now Chiara has a face
that Mikoy always talks about.

131
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:42,832
And I'm not surprised
why he keeps you hidden.

132
00:09:42,915 --> 00:09:44,417
Because with…

133
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:46,335
that beauty of yours,

134
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:47,837
a lot would try to steal you.

135
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,005
That's right.

136
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:50,923
You're good, Sianong.

137
00:09:51,007 --> 00:09:52,717
You're better than "alright".

138
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:55,636
- Alright is alright.
- That punchline was strong!

139
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,477
Alex? Where is he?

140
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,814
- Oh.
- Right, where is…

141
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:09,650
Wait, you know he's usually around here.

142
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:14,757
Wow!

143
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:15,841
Mikoy!

144
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:17,760
Alex!

145
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:38,239
Chiara the Valtrovi?

146
00:11:43,744 --> 00:11:47,832
Oh! I so love your earrings.
They're so beautiful!

147
00:11:52,628 --> 00:11:54,255
You're so fancy, girl!

148
00:11:54,338 --> 00:11:56,966
Well, my eye bags are as deep
as the Mariana Trench

149
00:11:57,049 --> 00:11:59,677
from working graveyard shifts
at the call center,

150
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:01,971
and I still can't afford Tom!

151
00:12:06,308 --> 00:12:08,811
What did you feed Chiara?

152
00:12:08,894 --> 00:12:11,230
Did you use some love potion from Quiapo?

153
00:12:11,313 --> 00:12:12,648
Huh? No way!

154
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:17,486
Don't tell me she fell
for your sexy dance moves?

155
00:12:18,988 --> 00:12:20,030
Uh…

156
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:22,783
No way! Come on!

157
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:24,118
And you said

158
00:12:24,201 --> 00:12:26,787
I could pass as Enrique Gil
on a rough day, right?

159
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:27,997
Right?

160
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,709
- Right?
- Yuck!

161
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:33,252
Oh my gosh!

162
00:12:33,335 --> 00:12:35,337
Hey guys, before anything else,

163
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:36,255
this is the old news,

164
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:40,634
Alex, Sianong.

165
00:12:41,844 --> 00:12:43,637
Chiara Valtrovi.

166
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:50,019
Wow, now he's speaking English
and being all sweet?

167
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:58,194
Wait.

168
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:03,699
You look familiar.

169
00:13:14,376 --> 00:13:18,088
Oh! No! No! You know, Chiara,
you're not gonna believe this.

170
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:20,090
Our friend Alex here…

171
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:22,134
She's really pretty, right?

172
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:24,011
She actually looks like a famous actress.

173
00:13:24,094 --> 00:13:24,929
Her name is…

174
00:13:25,596 --> 00:13:26,430
- Kim!
- Kim!

175
00:13:26,514 --> 00:13:29,308
- Dominguez.
- You idiot!

176
00:13:29,391 --> 00:13:30,434
Santo Domingo!

177
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,102
- Oh right! Santo Domingo!
- Ah, yes! Yes!

178
00:13:38,692 --> 00:13:40,736
It's always awkward at first when meeting.

179
00:13:40,819 --> 00:13:42,071
That's true!

180
00:13:42,154 --> 00:13:44,281
- Hey, guys, let's sit down.
- There!

181
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:48,744
- Let's go!
- Yes!

182
00:13:49,703 --> 00:13:51,622
You haven't slept yet, have you?

183
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:53,332
Yeah!

184
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:56,502
There!

185
00:13:58,629 --> 00:13:59,880
Does she know you?

186
00:14:01,423 --> 00:14:02,883
Luisa Mae.

187
00:14:04,468 --> 00:14:05,636
Or you're just her stalker?

188
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:07,388
I'm not a stalker!

189
00:14:12,268 --> 00:14:14,520
I'm just not sure if she knows me.

190
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:17,231
But of course, I know her.

191
00:14:18,148 --> 00:14:19,733
Everyone knows her.

192
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:23,153
That's why she's
the most popular girl in school.

193
00:14:23,988 --> 00:14:26,574
I'm sure you have a lot of rivals.

194
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:30,327
Wait! Why do you even like her?

195
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:34,290
Well,

196
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:38,836
there are a lot of reasons
why she's the popular girl in our school.

197
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:42,882
Aside from her beautiful face,

198
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:46,427
you know, she takes a lot of initiative

199
00:14:46,510 --> 00:14:49,013
with donation drives,
both inside and outside the school.

200
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:52,182
She also organizes
free food drives for strays,

201
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:54,602
free spaying and neutering
for cats and dogs,

202
00:14:54,685 --> 00:14:56,145
community pantries.

203
00:14:56,228 --> 00:14:59,732
She even holds job fairs
for senior citizens.

204
00:14:59,815 --> 00:15:02,026
And you know, she also fights for causes!

205
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:03,903
Wage increase.

206
00:15:03,986 --> 00:15:05,988
Lower prices of basic goods.

207
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:08,616
- Vote wisely for the country!
- Okay, fine! Fine! Fine!

208
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:10,034
She has everything.

209
00:15:10,117 --> 00:15:13,287
She was born with ube toppings
on top of her head.

210
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:18,667
She's the most special
of all special halo-halo!

211
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:28,469
Wait, Sophie.

212
00:15:32,222 --> 00:15:34,808
You still owe me a favor, right?

213
00:15:39,355 --> 00:15:42,942
Can you find a way for us to meet?

214
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:54,745
Tell us a story. How did you meet?

215
00:15:54,828 --> 00:15:57,122
But this time, from Chiara's POV.

216
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:58,290
Oh, right.

217
00:15:58,374 --> 00:15:59,458
We already know your side!

218
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:02,878
No, I think it's better
if we start with Alex.

219
00:16:04,004 --> 00:16:06,465
How did you and Mikoy meet?

220
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:12,638
Mikoy and I…

221
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:19,770
When I applied here in Manila for Prague,

222
00:16:19,853 --> 00:16:22,189
I worked part-time
as a waiter at a restaurant.

223
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:23,816
The two of them were always there.

224
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:26,026
That's where we met.

225
00:16:27,736 --> 00:16:29,279
Right! Right!

226
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:34,702
And honestly, I always had my eyes on him.

227
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:37,788
Even from afar,
I could sense that he's a fun guy,

228
00:16:37,871 --> 00:16:40,541
very sweet, and so fun to be with!

229
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:42,918
- Oh, right! Right!
- See?

230
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:45,129
He's really fun to be with.

231
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:47,756
Really?

232
00:16:48,424 --> 00:16:50,175
You're just hyping me up.

233
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:52,428
Right?

234
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:55,931
When we first met, you were kind of…

235
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:58,517
out of it!

236
00:16:59,101 --> 00:17:00,394
Right?

237
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:16,952
Wow!

238
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:19,913
You guys seem like such a fun group.

239
00:17:23,917 --> 00:17:29,173
How about we create fun memories with me?

240
00:17:33,927 --> 00:17:35,345
Go ahead, girl. What do you want?

241
00:17:58,452 --> 00:17:59,578
Oh…

242
00:17:59,661 --> 00:18:00,788
What are you doing?

243
00:18:01,371 --> 00:18:02,998
What else? I'm going to sleep.

244
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:06,126
I wasn't born
with ube toppings on my head,

245
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:08,212
so I need eight hours of sleep.

246
00:18:08,295 --> 00:18:09,588
At least that way,

247
00:18:09,671 --> 00:18:11,715
I'll have something decent
for the front page.

248
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:14,593
Didn't I already fix your room?

249
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:17,304
I already had it arranged
with the building service.

250
00:18:17,387 --> 00:18:19,098
Why don't you just stay there?

251
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:21,934
I've gotten used to it here.

252
00:18:22,017 --> 00:18:24,228
And if I go back there,

253
00:18:24,311 --> 00:18:26,522
I might not be able to sleep well.

254
00:18:27,648 --> 00:18:28,899
Not be able to sleep.

255
00:18:28,982 --> 00:18:30,943
That's not going to work anymore, Sophie.

256
00:18:31,026 --> 00:18:33,570
You need to get used to your own space.

257
00:18:36,615 --> 00:18:37,449
Wait.

258
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:40,119
Why are you making
such a big deal out of this?

259
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:44,581
What if someone sees us here?

260
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:46,458
What would they think?

261
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:49,211
Like, you know, we're dating.

262
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:53,966
You know how fast
rumors spread these days.

263
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:57,970
Why do you even care
about what other people say?

264
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:00,430
Are you a celebrity?

265
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:02,599
Or even an influencer?

266
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:04,852
It's not like that.

267
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:06,478
This is for you too.

268
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:08,397
What if someone likes you?

269
00:19:08,897 --> 00:19:11,233
Then they might think
you already have a boyfriend.

270
00:19:11,316 --> 00:19:13,735
Or they might think badly of you

271
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:15,654
because you sleep here.

272
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:17,823
Oh, please.

273
00:19:17,906 --> 00:19:21,243
I don't care about
what other people think.

274
00:19:21,326 --> 00:19:23,954
And besides, don't gaslight me.

275
00:19:24,037 --> 00:19:27,833
I know you're really just concerned
about yourself.

276
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:32,045
Because if your crush Luisa Mae
finds out about this,

277
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:33,672
it might ruin your plan.

278
00:19:34,715 --> 00:19:36,592
Fine, I'll just go sleep in my room.

279
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:40,179
You're really annoying.

280
00:19:47,811 --> 00:19:49,354
- Let's go!
- What a relief!

281
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:53,650
- Yes!
- Oh…

282
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:55,235
You can do it.

283
00:19:58,947 --> 00:20:00,073
Oh!

284
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:02,784
You can do it, Chiara! Like this.

285
00:20:05,412 --> 00:20:08,832
Then imagine your target is huge.

286
00:20:15,631 --> 00:20:17,966
Just beginner's luck.

287
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,136
My turn.

288
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:26,516
- Let's go!
- Okay, listen, Bok--

289
00:20:31,021 --> 00:20:32,773
Just in case you miss, okay?

290
00:20:32,856 --> 00:20:35,484
You need 170 points to win.

291
00:20:44,201 --> 00:20:45,702
Okay, okay.

292
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:51,083
Another triple twenty!

293
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:52,751
- Great follow-through!
- Alex, look!

294
00:20:52,834 --> 00:20:55,754
Alex, you just need a bullseye
for 170. Okay?

295
00:20:57,839 --> 00:21:01,093
If she doesn't hit a bullseye, she loses.

296
00:21:13,522 --> 00:21:15,357
- Oh my God. Triple 20.
- No way?

297
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:16,942
You're amazing!

298
00:21:17,025 --> 00:21:19,194
Let's go!

299
00:21:27,911 --> 00:21:31,248
Insane!

300
00:21:31,331 --> 00:21:33,208
You're so good!

301
00:21:42,092 --> 00:21:44,094
You probably think that just because

302
00:21:44,177 --> 00:21:47,222
Alex likes you so much,
she'll give in to you.

303
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:51,018
I actually I get it why you're friends.

304
00:21:51,101 --> 00:21:54,021
You're very competitive too, like Mikoy.

305
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:57,274
Back in Prague, he never wanted to lose
when we were drinking.

306
00:21:59,192 --> 00:22:01,486
But to be fair,
you really pushed me to my limit,

307
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:03,363
even though it was
my first time playing darts.

308
00:22:04,614 --> 00:22:08,452
Actually, we still
need to win Chiara back.

309
00:22:08,535 --> 00:22:10,245
In the game she's good at.

310
00:22:11,079 --> 00:22:12,414
- What's that?
- You see?

311
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:14,708
Wait a minute.

312
00:22:14,791 --> 00:22:15,917
What are you good at?

313
00:22:27,387 --> 00:22:29,014
What do you think?

314
00:22:29,097 --> 00:22:30,640
Is it effective?

315
00:22:30,724 --> 00:22:33,143
Do you think Chiara believes
we're really friends?

316
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:35,937
Of course!

317
00:22:36,021 --> 00:22:38,899
And those cutesy moves of yours
are something else.

318
00:22:38,982 --> 00:22:41,234
Honestly, it actually suits you.

319
00:22:41,318 --> 00:22:42,277
It's cute.

320
00:22:43,904 --> 00:22:45,906
That acting could win Oscars.

321
00:22:45,989 --> 00:22:48,950
You even made me believe
that you're really my friend.

322
00:22:51,536 --> 00:22:52,621
Why?

323
00:22:52,704 --> 00:22:54,331
Aren't we really friends?

324
00:22:58,543 --> 00:22:59,544
It's awesome.

325
00:22:59,628 --> 00:23:01,088
Well, fair enough.

326
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:05,675
Actually, it's kind of a privilege
to be friends with Kim Santo Domingo.

327
00:23:05,759 --> 00:23:07,928
Oops. Kim Dominguez, I mean.

328
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:09,638
You're unbelievable.

329
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:11,014
- Ouch.
- So dramatic.

330
00:23:11,098 --> 00:23:12,516
You should always be like this.

331
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:14,643
It really suits you.

332
00:23:18,396 --> 00:23:19,481
‪Then, suddenly--

333
00:23:41,962 --> 00:23:43,880
Yes, so much.

334
00:23:53,515 --> 00:23:56,059
He told you that, right?

335
00:23:58,103 --> 00:24:01,106
But we don't really talk about it.

336
00:24:01,189 --> 00:24:03,984
And I don't think we want
to talk about what happened.

337
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:15,162
I've actually been worried about Mikoy.

338
00:24:16,371 --> 00:24:20,375
I don't know, maybe
he's hiding something from me

339
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:23,545
or he's keeping things inside.

340
00:24:24,421 --> 00:24:28,550
But I guess he's just really such nice guy

341
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:32,387
who doesn't want me to worry,
so he doesn't talk about it.

342
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:36,099
But now that I've met you guys,

343
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:38,977
I feel relieved,

344
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:43,607
knowing he has friends he can rely on.

345
00:25:12,010 --> 00:25:14,512
You know what? Take care of Chiara.
She's really special.

346
00:25:16,306 --> 00:25:18,058
Let's do this more often.

347
00:25:35,909 --> 00:25:37,911
I'd rather just face
whatever happens to me here.

348
00:25:37,994 --> 00:25:39,579
<i>Even if I have to go all out</i>
<i>against the Moravianos.</i>

349
00:25:39,663 --> 00:25:41,915
<i>What I will never do is run and hide.</i>

350
00:25:41,998 --> 00:25:43,166
<i>I was born here in the Philippines.</i>

351
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:44,918
<i>And I will die here.</i>

